.LP
Gets the status of the process\&.
.LP
The value of \fIMisc\fR\& varies for different types of processes\&. For example, a \fIgen_server\fR\& process returns the callback module\&'s state, and a \fIgen_fsm\fR\& process returns information such as its current state name\&. Callback modules for \fIgen_server\fR\& and \fIgen_fsm\fR\& can also customise the value of \fIMisc\fR\& by exporting a \fIformat_status/2\fR\& function that contributes module-specific information; see \fBgen_server:format_status/2\fR\& and \fBgen_fsm:format_status/2\fR\& for more details\&.
.RE
